44
00:04:54,045 --> 00:04:56,838
on the 17th of July, 1738.

45
00:05:20,185 --> 00:05:22,078
It was his mother's fifth birth.

46
00:05:22,427 --> 00:05:25,117
She delivered them all here
under her fish stand.

47
00:05:25,221 --> 00:05:27,768
And all had been stillbirths,
or semi-stillbirths.

48
00:05:27,941 --> 00:05:28,942
Are you alright?

49
00:05:29,893 --> 00:05:32,411
And by evening, the whole mess
had been shoveled away...

50
00:05:32,481 --> 00:05:34,201
with the fish guts
into the river.

51
00:05:34,953 --> 00:05:36,851
It would be much the same today...

52
00:05:37,638 --> 00:05:39,058
but then...

53
00:05:39,646 --> 00:05:42,459
Jean-Baptiste chose differently.

54
00:06:14,889 --> 00:06:16,044
What's that noise?

55
00:06:16,674 --> 00:06:18,475
It's... it's a baby.

56
00:06:18,476 --> 00:06:19,782
What's going on here?

57
00:06:23,619 --> 00:06:26,402
- It's a newborn.
- Where's his mother?

58
00:06:27,852 --> 00:06:29,060
She was just here.

59
00:06:31,534 --> 00:06:36,710
She tried to kill it, her own child.
She tried to kill a baby!

60
00:06:38,528 --> 00:06:40,125
There! There she is!

61
00:06:40,376 --> 00:06:42,841
- Stop! Stop where you are!
- Murderer!

62
00:06:42,926 --> 00:06:46,454
Thus, the first sound
to escape Grenouille's lips...

63
00:06:47,037 --> 00:06:48,715
sent his mother
to the gallows.

64
00:06:52,509 --> 00:06:55,057
And Jean-Baptiste,
by official order...

65
00:06:55,949 --> 00:06:58,235
