00:36:01,813 --> 00:36:03,607
to detect the exact formula.

251
00:36:04,042 --> 00:36:08,442
Which notes, which cords.
And in what precise measurements.

252
00:36:09,856 --> 00:36:12,849
Could you tell me the exact formula
of "Amor and Psyche"ê?

253
00:36:15,510 --> 00:36:17,115
"Best nose in Paris".

254
00:36:22,439 --> 00:36:23,786
Speak up!

255
00:36:24,670 --> 00:36:27,732
You see, you can't, can you?
And I'll tell you why.

256
00:36:28,981 --> 00:36:31,516
Because talent means
next to nothing!

257
00:36:33,652 --> 00:36:36,151
While experience, acquired in humility...

258
00:36:36,662 --> 00:36:39,938
and hard work, means everything.

259
00:36:44,194 --> 00:36:46,665
I don't, I don't know
what a formula is.

260
00:36:46,867 --> 00:36:49,697
But I can make
"Amor and Psyche" for you now.

261
00:36:50,984 --> 00:36:54,058
And you think I'll just let you
slop around in my laboratory...

262
00:36:54,159 --> 00:36:56,053
with essential oils
that are worth a fortune?

263
00:36:56,389 --> 00:36:57,300
You?

264
00:36:58,406 --> 00:37:00,821
- Yes.
- Now pay attention!

265
00:37:04,072 --> 00:37:05,481
What is your name, anyway?

266
00:37:07,435 --> 00:37:09,117
Jean-Baptiste Grenouille.

267
00:37:11,875 --> 00:37:14,243
Very well, Jean-Baptiste Grenouille.

268
00:37:15,996 --> 00:37:19,271
You shall have the opportunity now,
this very moment, to prove your assertion.

269
00:37:19,324 --> 00:37:22,360
Your grandiose failure will also be
an opportunity for you to learn...

270
00:37:22,406 --> 00:37:25,597
- the virture of humility.
- How much do you want me to make?

271
00:37:25,647 --> 00:37:29,037
- How much of... what?
- How much "Amor and Psyche" do you want?

272
00:37:31,737 --> 00:37:35,567
- Shall I fill this flask?
- No! You shall not!

273
00:37:44,544 --> 00:37:47,106
- You may fill this one.
- Yes, master.

274
00:37:50,025 --> 00:37:52,154
- But, Master Baldini,
- Hmm?

275
00:37:52,498 --> 00:37:55,060
you must let me do it
in my own way.

276
00:37:55,510 --> 00:37:57,277
As you please.

277
00:38:03,508 --> 00:38:05,747
Don't drop that!
That's pure alcohol!

278
00:38:05,819 --> 00:38:07,961
You want to blow up
the entire building?

279
00:38:10,403 --> 00:38:12,032
You have to measure it first!

280
00:38:59,044 --> 00:39:02,356
Stop! Stop it!
That's enough! Basta!

281
00:39:02,741 --> 00:39:03,975
You know nothing!

282
00:39:04,446 --> 00:39:08,945
Essential oils are always to be
mixed first, then the alcohol added.

283
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:12,125
And never ever let this perfume
to be shaken like that.

284
00:39:12,411 --> 00:39:15,597
I must've been insane
to listen to your asinine gibberish.

285
00:39:17,455 --> 00:39:19,015
Yes, we're done.

286
00:39:47,645 --> 00:39:49,275
Mamamiya...

287
00:40:03,094 --> 00:40:05,324
This is "Amor and Psyche".

288
00:40:06,131 --> 00:40:08,384
But it's not a good perfume, master.

289
00:40:09,898 --> 00:40:13,251
If you let me again, master,
I'll make it more better.

290
00:41:25,241 --> 00:41:27,386
That's a really good perfume.

291
00:41:34,006 --> 00:41:36,116
Don't you want
to smell it, master?

292
00:41:36,167 --> 00:41:37,923
I'm not in the mood
to test it now.

293
00:41:37,972 --> 00:41:40,665
I have other things
on my mind. Go now.

294
00:41:42,453 --> 00:41:44,884
- But, master...
- Go now!

295
00:41:59,524 --> 00:42:02,424
Can't I come to work
for you, master, can't I?

296
00:42:04,535 --> 00:42:06,598
- Let me think about it.
- Master!

297
00:42:08,211 --> 00:42:11,215
I have to learn
how to keep smell.

298
00:42:12,643 --> 00:42:16,862
- What?
- Can you teach me that?

299
00:42:17,378 --> 00:42:19,561
I shall have to think
about it. Now go.

300
00:43:04,058 --> 00:43:05,572
I love you.

301
00:43:11,844 --> 00:43:14,277
I'll give you 50 francs for him.

302
00:43:21,329 --> 00:43:22,888
Grenouille!

303
00:43:22,930 --> 00:43:26,631
Grimal's transaction had
a profound effect on all three parties.

304
00:43:26,690 --> 00:43:27,711
Hey, watch out!

305
00:43:31,278 --> 00:43:34,270
Now at least, upon
Monsieur Grimal himself.

306
00:43:37,031 --> 00:43:38,731
As for Giuseppe Baldini,

307
00:43:38,799 --> 00:43:43,323
the acquisition of Grenouille miraculously
transformed his dwindling business,

308
00:43:43,389 --> 00:43:46,215
even surpassing
its former glory.

309
00:43:53,938 --> 00:43:55,994
While at last, for Jean-Baptiste,

310
00:43:56,308 --> 00:44:00,879
the mysterious secret
of the perfumers' craft began to unfold.

311
00:44:06,988 --> 00:44:09,470
Now, pay careful attention
to what I tell you.

312
00:44:09,520 --> 00:44:10,988
Just like a musical cord,

313
00:44:11,046 --> 00:44:14,799
a perfume cord contains
four essences, or notes,

314
00:44:14,858 --> 00:44:17,985
carefully selected
for their harmonic affinity.

315
00:44:18,042 --> 00:44:23,286
Each perfume contains three cords:
the head, the heart and the base,

316
00:44:23,323 --> 00:44:25,872
necessitating twelve notes in all.

317
00:44:26,467 --> 00:44:29,370
The head cord contains
the first impression,

318
00:44:29,428 --> 00:44:32,892
lasting only a few minutes,
before giving way to the heart cord:

319
00:44:32,950 --> 00:44:36,546
the theme of the perfume,
lasting several hours.

320
00:44:36,584 --> 00:44:39,207
Finally, the base cord:

321
00:44:39,527 --> 00:44:43,218
the trail of the perfume,
lasting several days.

322
00:44:47,440 --> 00:44:52,209
Mind you, the ancient Egyptians believed
that one can only create a truly original perfume...

323
00:44:52,274 --> 00:44:58,644
by adding an extra note,
one final essence that will ring out...

324
00:44:59,134 --> 00:45:01,292
and dominate the others.

325
00:45:03,470 --> 00:45:07,872
Legend has it that a jar
was once found in a pharaoh's tomb.

326
00:45:07,972 --> 00:45:11,495
And when it was opened,
a perfume was released.

327
00:45:11,615 --> 00:45:14,515
After all those thousands of years,

328
00:45:14,575 --> 00:45:18,481
a perfume of such subtle beauty,
and yet such power,

329
00:45:18,571 --> 00:45:21,391
that for one single moment,

330
00:45:21,447 --> 00:45:25,870
every single person on earth
believed they were in paradise.

331
00:45:27,490 --> 00:45:30,175
Twelve essences
could be identified.

332
00:45:31,158 --> 00:45:34,856
But the thirteenth,
the vital one...

333
00:45:36,313 --> 00:45:38,409
could never be determined.

334
00:45:40,121 --> 00:45:40,936
Why not?

335
00:45:43,342 --> 00:45:43,922
Why not??

336
00:45:44,144 --> 00:45:45,677
What do you mean why not?

337
00:45:46,847 --> 00:45:49,335
Because it's a legend, numskull.

338
00:45:50,570 --> 00:45:51,723
What's a legend?

339
00:45:54,294 --> 00:45:55,211
Never mind.

340
00:46:35,790 --> 00:46:38,226
Jean-Baptiste. Jean-Baptiste.

341
00:46:43,846 --> 00:46:45,080
What's the matter?

342
00:46:45,634 --> 00:46:49,407
I... I have to learn
how to capture a scent.

343
00:46:51,977 --> 00:46:53,424
What are you talking about?

344
00:46:53,921 --> 00:46:58,478
I have to learn how... how to
capture a scent and "reprose" it forever.

345
00:46:58,723 --> 00:47:01,736
- You mean "preserve".
- Yes, teach me that.

346
00:47:02,086 --> 00:47:05,477
Calm down, my boy.
Calm down.

347
00:47:06,037 --> 00:47:07,578
We have work to do.

348
00:47:09,273 --> 00:47:14,454
The soul of beings is their scent.
You said that, master.

349
00:47:15,765 --> 00:47:16,649
Did I?

350
00:47:17,103 --> 00:47:20,962
I will make as many perfumes as you want.
But you have to teach me...

351
00:47:21,218 --> 00:47:23,795
how to capture
the smell of all things.

352
00:47:25,163 --> 00:47:26,482
Can you do that?

353
00:47:27,826 --> 00:47:32,158
- Well, naturally.
- Then teach me everything you know.

354
00:47:35,352 --> 00:47:37,800
And I'll make you the best perfumer
in the whole world.

355
00:47:54,970 --> 00:47:56,837
Imagine, Jean-Baptiste:

356
00:47:56,895 --> 00:48:03,254
ten thousand roses to produce
one single ounce of essential oil.

357
00:48:05,013 --> 00:48:10,901
Now, keep them flowing,
for the bottom petals will be given to stew,

358
00:48:11,139 --> 00:48:12,727
while I set up the alembic.

359
00:48:12,771 --> 00:48:14,563
And take care.
Not to damage them.

360
00:48:14,824 --> 00:48:18,555
We have to let them go to
their deaths with their scent intact.

361
00:48:36,324 --> 00:48:39,677
Perfect! Now, help me
with the boiler set.

362
00:48:52,520 --> 00:48:55,831
Temperature is vital.
When the quicksilver is here,

363
00:48:55,908 --> 00:49:00,602
the heat is precisely correct,
and the oil will gradually rise.

364
00:49:01,950 --> 00:49:07,310
Note that this mechanism is
a remarkable invention of my own devising.

365
00:49:07,854 --> 00:49:13,521
You will observe how cold water
is pumped through here,

366
00:49:14,152 --> 00:49:19,001
allowing the essence
to condense here...

367
00:49:19,057 --> 00:49:20,922
until it finally...

368
00:49:22,085 --> 00:49:23,382
appears...

369
00:49:24,858 --> 00:49:26,113
here!

370
00:49:27,053 --> 00:49:33,153
Of course, out on the hillside above Grasse,
we had only to bellow pure fresh air.

371
00:49:34,156 --> 00:49:37,150
Ah, Grasse! What a town.

372
00:49:39,120 --> 00:49:44,540
The Rome of scents.
The Promised Land of perfume.

373
00:49:45,884 --> 00:49:50,215
No man can rightly
call himself a perfumer,

374
00:49:50,562 --> 00:49:54,744
unless he has proved his worth
in that hallowed place.

375
00:49:57,076 --> 00:49:59,683
Not to worry!
It happens all the time.

376
00:50:01,256 --> 00:50:02,895
To Grasse.

377
00:50:20,126 --> 00:50:21,178
Master.

378
00:50:22,358 --> 00:50:23,332
Look.

379
00:50:28,531 --> 00:50:30,900
The very soul of the rose.

380
00:51:22,881 --> 00:51:24,529
Jean-Baptiste.

381
00:51:27,370 --> 00:51:28,347
What's wrong?

382
00:51:29,779 --> 00:51:31,151
Jean-Baptiste.

383
00:51:34,185 --> 00:51:36,970
- What have you done?
- You lied.

384
00:51:37,308 --> 00:51:40,412
- What?
- You lied to me.

385
00:51:41,017 --> 00:51:43,772
How dare you
talk to me like that!

386
00:51:45,181 --> 00:51:47,788
You said I could capture
the scent of anything.

387
00:51:48,561 --> 00:51:49,947
And so you can!

388
00:51:53,828 --> 00:51:55,023
What do you smell?

389
00:51:56,214 --> 00:51:57,613
What do you smell?

390
00:52:02,832 --> 00:52:03,511
Nothing.

391
00:52:06,913 --> 00:52:10,233
- What were you expecting to smell?
- Glass.

392
00:52:10,920 --> 00:52:14,832
- But glass doesn't smell.
- Of course it does. What's this?

393
00:52:19,888 --> 00:52:21,403
I don't smell a thing.

394
00:52:22,225 --> 00:52:22,916
Basta!

395
00:52:22,968 --> 00:52:25,258
- Did you smell that copper?
- Enough!

396
00:52:28,233 --> 00:52:31,675
You were trying to distil
the smell of copper?

397
00:52:32,175 --> 00:52:33,011
iron...

398
00:52:33,064 --> 00:52:34,029
glass...

399
00:52:34,491 --> 00:52:35,754
copper...

400
00:52:39,265 --> 00:52:40,913
What else did you try?

401
00:52:44,674 --> 00:52:45,430
No!

402
00:52:47,618 --> 00:52:49,566
Have you gone completely insane?!

403
00:52:50,511 --> 00:52:52,550
You told me I had to experiment.

404
00:52:52,825 --> 00:52:57,806
Experiment? Experiment?
With a cat?!

405
00:53:00,880 --> 00:53:02,706
What kind of a human being are youê é?

406
00:53:03,319 --> 00:53:04,877
Don't you know anything?

407
00:53:05,204 --> 00:53:07,352
You can no more distil
the scent of a cat...

408
00:53:07,406 --> 00:53:09,811
than you can distil
the scent of you and me!

409
00:53:20,326 --> 00:53:23,105
- I can't?
- Of course not!

410
00:53:30,053 --> 00:53:31,675
He's in stadio ultimo.

411
00:53:31,729 --> 00:53:33,184
- What?
- He's dying.

412
00:53:33,240 --> 00:53:34,732
Is there nothing you can do?

413
00:53:35,260 --> 00:53:38,315
- I fear not.
- No! He cannot die.

414
00:53:38,372 --> 00:53:42,274
- Well, the fee is 50 francs.
- 50 francs? You're a charlatan!

415
00:53:48,012 --> 00:53:52,011
Oh dear, Jean-Baptiste!

416
00:53:53,092 --> 00:53:57,158
You cannot do this to me.
Please, don't die on me.

417
00:53:57,492 --> 00:53:59,723
Not now, not yet!

418
00:54:10,713 --> 00:54:12,905
Is there...

419
00:54:16,547 --> 00:54:18,493
any other way...

420
00:54:19,789 --> 00:54:22,608
to preserve smell
besides distil it?

421
00:54:23,007 --> 00:54:24,751
Jean-Baptiste...

422
00:54:29,517 --> 00:54:35,400
- Is there, master?
- Well, yes, I... I believe there is.

423
00:54:36,809 --> 00:54:38,689
What is ité?

424
00:54:40,445 --> 00:54:44,403
It is known as
the mysterious art of Enfleurage.

425
00:54:46,794 --> 00:54:48,408
Can you teach me?

426
00:54:51,418 --> 00:54:54,608
Not even I am intimate
with the secrets.

427
00:54:57,265 --> 00:54:59,682
But could I learn it in Grasse?

428
00:55:00,786 --> 00:55:03,535
- Well...
- Could I?

429
00:55:09,274 --> 00:55:12,429
Where else but in Grasse!

430
00:55:18,042 --> 00:55:20,350
Within a week, Grenouille was well again.

431
00:55:20,702 --> 00:55:23,364
But in order to travel to Grasse,
and find a job,

432
00:55:23,406 --> 00:55:25,966
he needed a journeyman's papers.

433
00:55:26,202 --> 00:55:28,018
Baldini agreed to provide them,

434
00:55:28,345 --> 00:55:34,052
on condition that Grenouille left him
not less than 100 formulas for new perfumes.

435
00:55:34,852 --> 00:55:38,948
Grenouille did not mind.
He could've given him a thousand.

436
00:55:44,279 --> 00:55:48,181
The morning of Grenouille's departure,
Baldini was pleased.

437
00:55:48,625 --> 00:55:52,566
At last, he felt rewarded
for his many years of hard work.

438
00:55:53,086 --> 00:55:56,171
He could not remember
a happier day.

439
00:55:56,369 --> 00:55:59,171
Deeply satisfied, he went
back to sleep...

440
00:55:59,656 --> 00:56:02,618
and awoke no more
in this life.

441
00:56:20,891 --> 00:56:25,626
With every step Grenouille took away
from the city, the happier he felt.

442
00:56:26,072 --> 00:56:30,786
The air above him grew
clearer, purer, cleaner.

443
00:56:30,916 --> 00:56:33,989
And at last, he was
able to breathe freely.

444
00:56:37,347 --> 00:56:39,936
There were two ways
to reach Grasse.

445
00:56:40,137 --> 00:56:43,649
The first followed the winding road
through the villages...

446
00:56:43,650 --> 00:56:46,658
while the second lay straight across
the hills and mountains,

447
00:56:46,715 --> 00:56:48,825
down into Provence.

448
00:56:49,817 --> 00:56:52,083
The choice was quite easy.

449
00:56:55,805 --> 00:57:00,634
Thus, his nose led him ever higher,
ever further from mankind.

450
00:57:01,037 --> 00:57:06,372
Ever more towards the magnetic pole
of the greatest possible solitude.

451
00:57:43,524 --> 00:57:44,897
Grenouille needed a moment...

452
00:57:44,949 --> 00:57:47,869
to believe that he had actually
found a spot on earth...

453
00:57:47,903 --> 00:57:50,724
where scent was almost absent.

454
00:57:55,725 --> 00:57:56,936
Spread all around...

455
00:57:56,999 --> 00:58:00,077
lay nothing but the tranquil
scent of dead stone.

456
00:58:03,272 --> 00:58:06,350
There was something
sacred about this place.

457
00:58:09,865 --> 00:58:12,471
No longer distracted
by anything external,

458
00:58:13,194 --> 00:58:17,751
he was finally able
to bask in his own existence.

459
00:58:19,164 --> 00:58:22,362
And found it splendid!

460
00:58:29,313 --> 00:58:33,569
After a while, he almost forgot
his plans and obsessions.

461
00:58:34,894 --> 00:58:38,393
And indeed,
might've done so altogether.

462
00:58:52,773 --> 00:58:53,951
Helloá.

463
00:58:57,896 --> 00:58:59,255
Helloá.

464
00:59:01,890 --> 00:59:03,338
Helloá.

465
00:59:20,135 --> 00:59:22,865
There were a thousand smells
in his clothes.

466
00:59:22,928 --> 00:59:25,842
The smell of sand, stone, moss...

467
00:59:25,881 --> 00:59:28,412
even the smell of the sausage
he'd eaten weeks ago.

468
00:59:28,882 --> 00:59:31,257
Only one smell was not there:

469
00:59:34,440 --> 00:59:35,877
His own.

470
01:00:11,404 --> 01:00:13,964
For the first time in his life,
Grenouille realized...

471
01:00:14,024 --> 01:00:16,523
that he had no smell of his own.

472
01:00:17,789 --> 01:00:19,276
He realized that all his life...

473
01:00:19,352 --> 01:00:21,700
he had been a nobody
to everyone.

474
01:00:22,895 --> 01:00:26,574
What he now felt
was the fear of his own oblivion.

475
01:00:27,259 --> 01:00:28,881
It was as though...

476
01:00:29,044 --> 01:00:30,922
he did not exist.

477
01:00:36,102 --> 01:00:40,247
By the first light of next morning,
Grenouille had a new plan.

478
01:00:40,637 --> 01:00:43,450
He must continue
his journey to Grasse.

479
01:00:43,770 --> 01:00:47,167
There he would teach the world
not only that he existed...

480
01:00:47,238 --> 01:00:48,866
that he was someone...

481
01:00:49,193 --> 01:00:51,696
but that he was exceptional.

482
01:00:55,576 --> 01:00:57,226
And with this decision,

483
01:00:57,629 --> 01:01:01,732
it seemed that the gods
had at last begun to smile on him.

484
01:05:18,257 --> 01:05:19,521
Laura?

485
01:05:26,906 --> 01:05:28,141
Laura?

486
01:05:28,918 --> 01:05:30,684
Coming, papa.

487
01:06:05,775 --> 01:06:08,042
Haven't seen you here before.

488
01:06:09,523 --> 01:06:11,192
It's my first season.

489
01:06:12,621 --> 01:06:14,690
Picking together
is always more fun.

490
01:06:16,034 --> 01:06:18,177
They say you pick
everything you find.

491
01:07:00,816 --> 01:07:04,745
Idiot! How many times do I told you
not to cram the blossoms in...

492
01:07:04,781 --> 01:07:06,468
like you're stuffing a chicken?

493
01:07:07,939 --> 01:07:09,633
Watch how Grenouille does it.

494
01:07:11,606 --> 01:07:15,547
Look how skillfully he handles them.
The whole art of Enflourage...

495
01:07:15,585 --> 01:07:19,507
is to allow the flowers to die slowly,
in their sleep as it were...

496
01:07:19,834 --> 01:07:24,587
handle them as you would a lady.
Wouldn't you agree with me, Druot?

497
01:07:25,036 --> 01:07:26,810
If you say so, madame.

498
01:07:29,333 --> 01:07:31,921
You! Check the jonquil blossoms.

